Distribution (
Fig. 23
):
Probably endemic to the south-western Cape, from the southern Swartland (Kasteelberg) south to the Cape Peninsula and east to the central Langeberge. Literature records (
Connolly 1939
) from further east (E. Cape and Lesotho , see Appendix 2 ) must be considered dubious. It seems probable that these represent misidentified specimens.
